<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Well, after I reached lvl 40 with my merc and did the 2 hour long epic quest (almost all traveling time), I deciding I need a change of pace, so I started a Sorcerer, just because not enough people play them, and I have this unhealthy attraction to classes that are regarded as useless because other classes can do anything thing can, but better.<P>Anyway, I'm at lvl 8 now, 7 spec mind, 3 spec body (going to spec body for next few lvls), and while it's nice not having to play an entire day for 1 lvl, I really don't know too much about playing them or any caster class. Hence, I'm asking for advice here.<P>So....you highish lvl Sorcerers out there...<BR>Have any tips?<BR>Advanced Strategies?<BR>Playing Styles?<BR>Favorite pets?<BR>Pets that don't seem humanoid that you can still charm?<BR>Best areas to hunt because of high pet conc?<BR>etc, etc.<P>Anything you can think of, because I'm totally clueless    <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"><P><BR>Edit: What does the acronym DOT stand for? I've seen it around, but as I said before, I have no experience with caster classes.
