<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Lesson 2: Group with a Friar<BR>Why?<BR>Friars can heal and buff your pet. I have been grouping with my Friar friends for 10 levels now. We take out reds with no problem at all and our downtime is not even worth being mentioned  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><BR>Moreover grouping with a Friar makes one spell that is hardly ever used VERY useful: Amnesia. Look at the following scenario:<BR>- red mob is pulled (preferably with debuff)<BR>- Friar takes aggro, Pet helps as good as it can<BR>- Friar gets low on hp<BR>- trigger the hotkey you made before saying: Stop attacking, casting AMNESIA<BR>- Friar stopps attacking<BR>- you cast Amnesia and the mob forgets who hurt it most so far<BR>- pet hits mob, gets aggro<BR>- Friar heals himself and steps back into battle<P>--------------------<P>Cay - Slave Driver on Gawaine
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
