Lesson 5: Be wise about your choice of prey<BR>What kind of mob you hunt does matter a LOT. Let your pet attack a caster mob and a melee mob. The difference you see is devastating. DOTs (damage over time spells, i.e. poisoning) have more effect on mammals (furry creatures like horses). Hunt humanoid creatures: for one they drop coin (which will procrostinate the need to go sell considerably) and in case your pet dies or is low on health it can be replaced quickly.<P>--------------------<P>Cay - Slave Driver on Gawaine
</FONT>
