<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I kept mind and body roughly equal as I leveled, and I was pretty happy with that combo. I never had trouble getting a yellow pet  (well, no trouble from the level of my mind spec), and the better damage from the spec dd is handy for finishing fights faster. Soloing, I'd send in the pet, then dot, nuke nuke nuke, quickcast lifedrain (after it hit me) and it would usually be dead. Sometimes I'd have to use my staff.<P>Grouping is good, but beware mezing. Lower level chars don't /assist so well, and mez time is pretty short to begin with. If you are outside, stand a little ways away from the group and mez during the pull. Tanks will usually only hit the ones that make it to the group. They'll leave the mezed one alone if it is out of range. If the extra gets to the group, you can pretty much expect mez to get broken.<P>Also, don't be within melee range of the monster when someone breaks mez. It will take one swipe at you if it can before turning to the mez breaker. <P>Good luck!<BR>--Winin
</FONT>
