<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Aye, the "nuke" is the mind blast (body spec direct damage spell). I really hate downtime, so I try to stick with the power efficient spells. Actually, the dot takes a lot of power, so I don't usually use it unless.<P>I try to do mostly mind blasts, but if they are resisted a lot, I switch to lifedrains, but if they are resisted too, I'll try the baseline dot. For tougher foes however, I'll start with the dot so I get the extra damage in. For really tough ones, I'll root, then debuff, then dot, nuke nuke, etc.<P>With your body spec at ~2/3 of your level, the spec nuke will do a little more damage than the lifedrain, and it will cost less power. The damage will vary of course depending on monster type (some resist mind spells better than lifedrains).<BR>--Winin
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
