One thing I noticed last night while my group pulled Danonin Clerks.  <P>On the initial pull, none of them came for me until I started to cast a spell - then one would veer off its present path and come for me.  I would stay away from the group and wait for the other caster and cleric (we had two clerics, one casting smite) to start to cast, then I would use the single target mezz on the two that went for them.  On the rare resist, the clerk would head for the paladin who is in between me and the healing cleric, a good distance away from either of us.  This strategy worked very well, and most of the clerks were orange and red with some purple.  We had 6 people in the group, only two tin heads.<P>--------------------<P>Malachai Mindbender<BR>Enigmatic of Avalon - Guinivere<BR>Sanguis Societat<BR>http://www.farrout.net/sanguis/memberlist.asp?memberID=8
